=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LeastChange_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright mixed sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 50 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.3301
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9445
  pitch_clarity: 16.8013
  inharmonicity: 0.0325
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -17.0926
  resonance_freq: 6093.8965

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LeastChange Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LeastChange.html
// Tags: LeastChange, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
(
d = { |amp = 1.0|
    var in1, in2;
    in1 = LFNoise0.ar(800, amp);
    in2 = SinOsc.ar(800);
    LeastChange.ar(in1, in2) * 0.1;
}.play;
)

d.set(\amp, 0.1);
d.set(\amp, 0);
d.set(\amp, 3);
d.free;
